To uee the OPAL implementation of Opacity, lines like the following
should be added to the flash.par files.
(This is an example and may need to be completed.)

And the necessary OPAL table files (NOT provided with the FLASH code
release) need to be placed where they can be read by FLASH, of course.


op_opalTableAbundMax_3  = 0.35
op_opalTableAbundMax_4  = 0.5
op_opalTableAbundMax_5  = 0.7
op_opalTableAbundMax_6  = 0.8
op_opalTableAbundMax_7  = 0.9
op_opalTableAbundMax_8  = 0.95
op_opalTableAbundMax_9  = 0.98

op_opalTableLowT_1            = "lowT_fa05_gs98_z2m2_x00.data"
op_opalTableLowT_2            = "lowT_fa05_gs98_z2m2_x10.data"
op_opalTableLowT_3            = "lowT_fa05_gs98_z2m2_x20.data"
op_opalTableLowT_5            = "lowT_fa05_gs98_z2m2_x50.data"
#...
op_opalTableLowT_10            = "lowT_fa05_gs98_z2m2_x98.data"
op_opalTableHighT_1            = "gs98_z2m2_x00.data"
op_opalTableHighT_2            = "gs98_z2m2_x10.data"
op_opalTableHighT_3            = "gs98_z2m2_x20.data"
op_opalTableHighT_4            = "gs98_z2m2_x35.data"
op_opalTableHighT_5            = "gs98_z2m2_x50.data"
#...
op_opalTableHighT_10            = "gs98_z2m2_x98.data"
